				Dear Participant,<br><br>
 
				This study is designed by two final year MA (Hons) Psychology and Business students at the University of Edinburgh.<br><br>
 
The aim of this project is to explore the magnitude of executive functions and eating habits.  This dissertation project is created in order to enhance further understanding of association between human cognition and eating choices.<br><br>
 
Your participation in this project will require approximately 40 minutes in which environmental distractions should be avoided in order to achieve reliable reflection of your choices and abilities.<br><br>

By completing this survey you indicate that you understand the following:<br>
<ul>
<li>It is not anticipated that you will experience any discomfort from answering the questions</li>
<li>Any information you provide during the study will be treated with strict confidence and it will not be possible to identify individuals. The data will be collected and stored in accordance with the Data Protection Act (1998)</li>
<li>You may refuse to participate or withdraw from participation without evaluation or consequence at any time</li>
<li>This survey is for people of 18 years and above</li>
<li>This survey should be completed individually</li>
</ul>
Thank you for your time and cooperation
Yours sincerely,
Nyssa Gaba and Alicja Janowska


I agree to participate in the research study. I understand the purpose and nature of this study and I am participating voluntarily. I understand that I can withdraw from the study at any time, without any penalty or consequences.				
